{"BREACH":[{"def":"A hernia; a rupture.","pos":""}],"BREACHY":[{"def":"Apt to break fences or to break out of pasture; unruly; as, breachy cattle.","pos":""}],"BREAD":[{"def":"An article of food made from flour or meal by moistening, kneading, and baking.","pos":""},{"def":"Food; sustenance; support of life, in general.","pos":""}],"BREADCORN":[{"def":"Corn of grain of which bread is made, as wheat, rye, etc.","pos":""}],"BREADFRUIT":[{"def":"The tree itself, which is one of considerable size, with large, lobed leaves.","pos":""}],"BREADLESS":[{"def":"Without bread; destitude of food.","pos":""}],"BREADROOT":[{"def":"The root of a leguminous plant (Psoralea esculenta), found near the Rocky Mountains.","pos":""}],"BREADSTUFF":[{"def":"Grain, flour, or meal of which bread is made.","pos":""}],"BREADTH":[{"def":"Distance from side to side of any surface or thing; measure across, or at right angles to the length; width.","pos":""}],"BREADTHLESS":[{"def":"Without breadth.","pos":""}],"BREADTHWISE":[{"def":"In the direction of the breadth.","pos":""}],"BREADWINNER":[{"def":"The member of a family whose labor supplies the food of the family; one who works for his living.","pos":""}],"BREAK":[{"def":"To strain apart; to sever by fracture; to divide with violence; as, to break a rope or chain; to break a seal; to break an axle; to break rocks or coal; to break a lock.","pos":""},{"def":"To lay open as by breaking; to divide; as, to break a package of goods.","pos":""}],"BREAK-CIRCUIT":[{"def":"A key or other device for breaking an electrical circuit.","pos":""}],"BREAK-UP":[{"def":"Disruption; a separation and dispersion of the parts or members; as, a break-up of an assembly or dinner party; a break-up of the government.","pos":""}],"BREAKABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being broken.","pos":""}],"BREAKAGE":[{"def":"The act of breaking; a break; a breaking; also, articles broken.","pos":""},{"def":"An allowance or compensation for things broken accidentally, as in transportation or use.","pos":""}],"BREAKAWAY":[{"def":"A wild rush of sheep, cattle, horses, or camels (especially at the smell or the sight of water); a stampede.","pos":""}],"BREAKDOWN":[{"def":"The act or result of breaking down, as of a carriage; downfall.","pos":""}],"BREAKER":[{"def":"A small water cask.","pos":""}],"BREAKFAST":[{"def":"The first meal in the day, or that which is eaten at the first meal.","pos":""},{"def":"A meal after fasting, or food in general.","pos":""}],"BREAKNECK":[{"def":"A fall that breaks the neck.","pos":""},{"def":"A steep place endangering the neck.","pos":""}],"BREAKWATER":[{"def":"Any structure or contrivance, as a mole, or a wall at the mouth of a harbor, to break the force of waves, and afford protection from their violence.","pos":""}],"BREAM":[{"def":"A European fresh-water cyprinoid fish of the genus Abramis, little valued as food.","pos":""},{"def":"An American fresh-water fish, of various species of Pomotis and allied genera, which are also called sunfishes and pondfishes.","pos":""}],"BREAST":[{"def":"The fore part of the body, between the neck and the belly; the chest; as, the breast of a man or of a horse.","pos":""},{"def":"Either one of the protuberant glands, situated on the front of the chest or thorax in the female of man and of some other mammalia, in which milk is secreted for the nourishment of the young; a mammma; a teat.","pos":""}],"BREAST-DEEP":[{"def":"Deep as from the breast to the feet; as high as the breast.","pos":""}],"BREAST-HIGH":[{"def":"High as the breast.","pos":""}],"BREASTBAND":[{"def":"A band for the breast.","pos":""}],"BREASTBEAM":[{"def":"The front transverse beam of a locomotive.","pos":""}],"BREASTBONE":[{"def":"The bone of the breast; the sternum.","pos":""}],"BREASTED":[{"def":"Having a breast; -- used in composition with qualifying words, in either a literal or a metaphorical sense; as, a single-breasted coat.","pos":""}],"BREASTFAST":[{"def":"A large rope to fasten the midship part of a ship to a wharf, or to another vessel.","pos":""}],"BREASTHEIGHT":[{"def":"The interior slope of a fortification, against which the garnison lean in firing.","pos":""}],"BREASTHOOK":[{"def":"A thick piece of timber in the form of a knee, placed across the stem of a ship to strengthen the fore part and unite the bows on each side.","pos":""}],"BREASTING":[{"def":"The curved channel in which a breast wheel turns.","pos":""}],"BREASTKNOT":[{"def":"A pin worn of the breast for a fastening, or for ornament; a brooch.","pos":""}],"BREASTPIN":[{"def":"A pin worn on the breast for a fastening, or for ornament; a brooch.","pos":""}],"BREASTPLATE":[{"def":"A part of the vestment of the high priest, worn upon the front of the ephod.","pos":""},{"def":"A kind of plow, driven by the breast of the workman; -- used to cut or pare turf.","pos":""}],"BREASTRAIL":[{"def":"The upper rail of any parapet of ordinary height, as of a balcony; the railing of a quarter-deck, etc.","pos":""}],"BREASTSUMMER":[{"def":"A summer or girder extending across a building flush with, and supporting, the upper part of a front or external wall; a long lintel; a girder; -- used principally above shop windows.","pos":""}],"BREASTWHEEL":[{"def":"A water wheel, on which the stream of water strikes neither so high as in the overshot wheel, nor so low as in the undershot, but generally at about half the height of the wheel, being kept in contact with it by the breasting.","pos":""}],"BREASTWORK":[{"def":"A defensive work of moderate height, hastily thrown up, of earth or other material.","pos":""},{"def":"A railing on the quarter-deck and forecastle.","pos":""}],"BREATH":[{"def":"The air inhaled and exhaled in respiration, air which, in the process of respiration, has parted with oxygen and has received carbonic acid, aqueous vapor, warmth, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"The act of breathing naturally or freely; the power or capacity to breathe freely; as, I am out of breath.","pos":""}],"BREATHABLE":[{"def":"Such as can be breathed.","pos":""}],"BREATHABLENESS":[{"def":"State of being breathable.","pos":""}],"BREATHE":[{"def":"To respire; to inhale and exhale air; hence;, to live.","pos":""},{"def":"To take breath; to rest from action.","pos":""}],"BREATHER":[{"def":"One who breathes.","pos":""},{"def":"That which puts one out of breath, as violent exercise.","pos":""}],"BREATHFUL":[{"def":"Full of breath; full of odor; fragrant.","pos":""}],"BREATHING":[{"def":"A mark to indicate aspiration or its absence.","pos":""}],"BREATHLESS":[{"def":"Spent with labor or violent action; out of breath.","pos":""},{"def":"Not breathing; holding the breath, on account of fear, expectation, or intense interest; attended with a holding of the breath; as, breathless attention.","pos":""}],"BREATHLESSLY":[{"def":"In a breathless manner.","pos":""}],"BREATHLESSNESS":[{"def":"The state of being breathless or out of breath.","pos":""}],"BRECCIA":[{"def":"A rock composed of angular fragments either of the same mineral or of different minerals, etc.","pos":""}],"BRECCIATED":[{"def":"Consisting of angular fragments cemented together; resembling breccia in appearance.","pos":""}],"BRED":[{"def":"BREDE; BREEDE Brede, or Breede, n.","pos":""}],"BREDE":[{"def":"Half lapped in glowing gauze and golden brede.","pos":""}],"BREECH":[{"def":"The external angle of knee timber, the inside of which is called the throat.","pos":""}],"BREECH ACTION":[{"def":"The breech mechanism in breech-loading small arms and certain special guns, as automatic and machine guns; --used frequently in referring to the method by which the movable barrels of breech- loading shotguns are locked, unlocked, or rotated to loading position.","pos":""}],"BREECH SIGHT":[{"def":"A device attached to the breech of a firearm, to guide the eye, in conjunction with the front sight, in taking aim.","pos":""}],"BREECH-LOADING":[{"def":"Receiving the charge at the breech instead of at the muzzle.","pos":""},{"def":"A strong iron or steel plug screwed into the breech of a musket or other firearm, to close the bottom of the bore.","pos":""}],"BREECHBLOCK":[{"def":"The movable piece which closes the breech of a breech-loading firearm, and resists the backward force of the discharge.","pos":""}],"BREECHCLOTH":[{"def":"A cloth worn around the breech.","pos":""}],"BREECHES":[{"def":"A garment worn by men, covering the hips and thighs; smallclothes.","pos":""},{"def":"Trousers; pantaloons.","pos":""}],"BREECHING":[{"def":"A strong rope rove through the cascabel of a cannon and secured to ringbolts in the ship's side, to limit the recoil of the gun when it is discharged.","pos":""}],"BREECHLOADER":[{"def":"A firearm which receives its load at the breech.","pos":""}],"BREED":[{"def":"To produce as offspring; to bring forth; to bear; to procreate; to generate; to beget; to hatch.","pos":""},{"def":"To take care of in infancy, and through the age of youth; to bring up; to nurse and foster.","pos":""}],"BREEDBATE":[{"def":"One who breeds or originates quarrels.","pos":""}],"BREEDER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, breeds, produces, brings up, etc.","pos":""}],"BREEDING":[{"def":"A fly of various species, of the family Tabanidæ, noted for buzzing about animals, and tormenting them by sucking their blood; -- called also horsefly, and gadfly.","pos":""}],"BREEZE":[{"def":"A light, gentle wind; a fresh, soft-blowing wind.","pos":""},{"def":"An excited or ruffed state of feeling; a flurry of excitement; a disturbance; a quarrel; as, the discovery produced a breeze.","pos":""}],"BREEZELESS":[{"def":"Motionless; destitute of breezes.","pos":""}],"BREEZINESS":[{"def":"State of being breezy.","pos":""}],"BREEZY":[{"def":"Characterized by, or having, breezes; airy.","pos":""},{"def":"Fresh; brisk; full of life.","pos":""}],"BREGMA":[{"def":"The point of junction of the coronal and sagittal sutures of the skull.","pos":""}],"BREGMATIC":[{"def":"Pertaining to the bregma.","pos":""}],"BREHON":[{"def":"An ancient Irish or Scotch judge.","pos":""}],"BRELAN CARRE":[{"def":"In French games, a double pair royal.","pos":""}],"BRELAN FAVORI":[{"def":"In French games, a pair royal composed of 2 cards in the hand and the card turned.","pos":""}],"BRELOQUE":[{"def":"A seal or charm for a watch chain.","pos":""}],"BREME":[{"def":"Fierce; sharp; severe; cruel.","pos":""},{"def":"Famous; renowned; well known.","pos":""}],"BRENNAGE":[{"def":"A tribute which tenants paid to their lord, in lieu of bran, which they were obliged to furnish for his hounds.","pos":""}],"BRENNINGLY":[{"def":"Burningly; ardently.","pos":""}],"BREST":[{"def":"BREST; BREAST Brest, Breast, n.","pos":""}],"BRESTSUMMER":[{"def":"See Breastsummer.","pos":""}],"BRETHREN":[{"def":"Note: This form of the plural is used, for the most part, in solemn address, and in speaking of religious sects or fraternities, or their members.","pos":""}],"BRETON":[{"def":"Of or relating to Brittany, or Bretagne, in France.","pos":""},{"def":"A native or inhabitant of Brittany, or Bretagne, in France; also, the ancient language of Brittany; Armorican.","pos":""}],"BRETT":[{"def":"Same as Britzska.","pos":""}],"BRETTICE":[{"def":"The wooden boarding used in supporting the roofs and walls of coal mines.","pos":""}],"BRETWALDA":[{"def":"The official title applied to that one of the Anglo-Saxon chieftains who was chosen by the other chiefs to lead them in their warfare against the British tribes.","pos":""}],"BREVE":[{"def":"A note or character of time, equivalent to two semibreves or four minims.","pos":""},{"def":"Any writ or precept under seal, issued out of any court.","pos":""}],"BREVET":[{"def":"A commission giving an officer higher rank than that for which he receives pay; an honorary promotion of an officer.","pos":""}],"BREVETCY":[{"def":"The rank or condition of a brevet officer.","pos":""}],"BREVIARY":[{"def":"An abridgment; a compend; an epitome; a brief account or summary.","pos":""},{"def":"A book containing the daily public or canonical prayers of the Roman Catholic or of the Greek Church for the seven canonical hours, namely, matins and lauds, the first, third, sixth, and ninth hours, vespers, and compline; -- distinguished from the missal.","pos":""}],"BREVIATE":[{"def":"A short compend; a summary; a brief statement.","pos":""},{"def":"A lawyer's brief.","pos":""}],"BREVIATURE":[{"def":"An abbreviature; an abbreviation.","pos":""}],"BREVIER":[{"def":"A size of type between bourgeous and minion.","pos":""}],"BREVILOQUENCE":[{"def":"A brief and pertinent mode of speaking.","pos":""}],"BREVIPED":[{"def":"Having short legs.","pos":""},{"def":"A breviped bird.","pos":""}],"BREVIPEN":[{"def":"A brevipennate bird.","pos":""}],"BREVIPENNATE":[{"def":"Short-winged; -- applied to birds which can not fly, owing to their short wings, as the ostrich, cassowary, and emu.","pos":""},{"def":"Short-billed; having a short beak.","pos":""}],"BREVITY":[{"def":"Shortness of duration; briefness of time; as, the brevity of human life.","pos":""},{"def":"Contraction into few words; conciseness.","pos":""}],"BREW":[{"def":"To boil or seethe; to cook.","pos":""},{"def":"To prepare, as beer or other liquor, from malt and hops, or from other materials, by steeping, boiling, and fermentation.","pos":""}],"BREWAGE":[{"def":"Malt liquor; drink brewed.","pos":""}],"BREWER":[{"def":"One who brews; one whose occupation is to prepare malt liquors.","pos":""}],"BREWERY":[{"def":"A brewhouse; the building and apparatus where brewing is carried on.","pos":""}],"BREWHOUSE":[{"def":"A house or building appropriated to brewing; a brewery.","pos":""}],"BREWING":[{"def":"A gathering or forming of a storm or squall, indicated by thick, dark clouds.","pos":""}],"BREWIS":[{"def":"Broth or pottage.","pos":""},{"def":"Bread soaked in broth, drippings of roast meat, milk, or water and butter.","pos":""}],"BREWSTERITE":[{"def":"A rare zeolitic mineral occurring in white monoclinic crystals with pearly luster.","pos":""}]}